608	\begin{remark}[Use in the LES finite-length transport, queued for iter-044+]
609	  After iter-042 the cover-evaluation chain consumes a single uniform $\Module\,k$-finite predicate at every degree. For an \lstinline{AffineCoverMVSquare} $S$ with corners $X_1, X_2, X_3$ affine and $X_4 = \top$, given \lstinline{IsAffineHModuleHomFinite k C F} and \lstinline{IsAffineHModuleVanishing k C F},
610	  \begin{enumerate}
611	    \item For each affine corner $X_j$ ($j = 1, 2, 3$) and each degree $i \ge 0$, $\HModulePrime^i(X_j)$ is $\Module\,k$-finite by Theorem~\ref{thm:Scheme_module_finite_HModule_prime_of_affine} (iter-042) — one class lookup, no per-degree case-split at the call site.
612	    \item The iter-029/030 LES specialised to $S$ then forces $\HModulePrime^i(X_4)$ to be a $\Module\,k$-finite extension of $\Module\,k$-finite pieces (queued for iter-044+ — bridges $\AddCommGrpCat$-side LES exactness to $k$-linear \lstinline{Function.Exact}).
613	    \item The iter-035 corner-bridge identifies $\HModulePrime^i(X_4)$ with $\HModule\,k\,F\,i$, and iter-037's transport carries the finiteness across — landing $\Module.\mathrm{Finite}\,k\,(\HModule\,k\,(\toModuleKSheaf\,C)\,1)$, the genus carrier (Definition~\ref{def:genus}).
614	  \end{enumerate}
615	  Iter-043+ produces the carrier instances \lstinline{IsAffineHModuleHomFinite k C (toModuleKSheaf C)} (via Stein-factorization-derived $\Gamma(\Spec A, \struct C) \simeq A$ on affine corners of a finite-type $k$-scheme) and \lstinline{IsAffineHModuleVanishing k C (toModuleKSheaf C)} (via project-local Čech-vs-derived comparison + affine Čech vanishing).
616	\end{remark}
